  "texts": [
    "Informativeness seeks to maximize the amount of information from deciding the sample and information source to query.",
    "Thus, the learner might privilege the evaluations from accurate and yet costly oracles to capitalize from high-quality information and potentially reach the objective. 2.",
    "Representativeness attempts to identify underlying structures of the domain to better inform the search procedure.",
    "In this case, the decision making process might prefer to interrogate less expensive sources of information to contain the required effort, especially if cheap predictions of the target distribution exhibit good correlation with the estimate of the accurate oracle. 3.",
    "Diversity scatters the sampling effort over the domain to pursue a proper distribution of evaluations and augment the awareness about the target distribution."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}